[Elsewhere in the United Kingdom (Scotland and Northern Ireland),
where rates of vaccine uptake have been higher, rates of measles
infection have been lower. Overall uptake of the MMR vaccine in
Scotland remains high, with 91.7 percent of 2-year-olds and 94.9
percent of 5-year-olds having been immunised with at least one dose
of MMR, to protect them against measles, mumps and rubella.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the United Kingdom can
be accessed at:
<http://healthmap.org/promed/en?v=54.5,-2,5>.
